                             ===Issue===                                               
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                   
                             # Evaluation Report                                       
                                                                                       
                             ## Summary                                                
                                                                                       
                             The fuzzing campaign, driven by                           
                             libFuzzer, terminated with an ERROR:                     
                             libFuzzer: timeout message, indicating                   
                             that the fuzzer exceeded its allotted                     
                             execution time without completing its                     
                             intended coverage goals or finding a                      
                             crash.                                                    
                                                                                       
                             ## Description                                            
                                                                                       
                             - Issue Overview                                          
                                During a libFuzzer run, the process                   
                             hit a predefined timeout threshold and                    
                             was forcefully aborted.                                   
                                The error message ERROR: libFuzzer:                  
                             timeout is the only indicator provided                   
                             by the issue report.                                      
                                                                                       
                             - Vulnerability Type                                      
                                No specific vulnerability type (e.g.,                 
                             memory corruption, infinite loop,                         
                             resource exhaustion) is mentioned in the                  
                             issue.                                                    
                                                                                       
                             - Key Observations and Findings                           
                                The fuzzer harness served as the                      
                             entry point but is not identified as the                  
                             root cause.                                               
                                A timeout suggests either extremely                   
                             long execution paths, blocking                            
                             operations, or lack of new coverage,                      
                             causing the fuzzer to stall.                              
                                There is no indication of a crash or                  
                             undefined behavioronly that the fuzzing                  
                             session did not complete in time.                         
                                No logs of inputs or execution traces                 
                             at the point of timeout are provided.                     
                                                                                       
                             - Areas for Investigation                                 
                                Fuzzer Harness Code: Review the fuzz                  
                             entry function to confirm it handles its                  
                             inputs efficiently and returns control                    
                             promptly.                                                 
                                Target Modules: Identify the APIs,                    
                             libraries, or modules that the fuzzer is                  
                             exercising; inspect for long-running                      
                             loops, blocking I/O, or heavy                             
                             computations.                                             
                                Timeout Configuration: Check the                      
                             fuzzers invocation parameters (e.g.,                     
                             -timeout, runs, corpus settings) to                      
                             understand the threshold that was                         
                             exceeded.                                                 
                                Coverage Reports and Logs: Examine                    
                             any coverage data or partial logs                         
                             generated before the timeout to pinpoint                  
                             where execution time accumulates.                         
                                Resource Usage Patterns: Profile CPU,                 
                             memory, and I/O usage during fuzzing to                   
                             see if resource contention contributed to                 
                             the delay.                                                
                                                                                       
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                      
                             Here is the initial issue log of the                      
                             codebase:                                                 
                             <issue>                                                   
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             </issue>                                                  
                             ===Analysis Report===                                     
                             # Analysis Report                                         
                                                                                       
                             ## Relevant Code Snippets                                 
                             <code_snippets>

                             112:    public void dump(byte[] data, int

                             ```                                                       
                             </code>

                             112:    public void dump(byte[] data, int                 
                             offset, int length, int padding) throws                   
                             IOException {                                             
                             113:        int pos = offset;

                             length - HEADER_SIZE)){

                             ## Fix Strategy                                           
                             <fix_strategy>                                            
                                                                                       
                             1. Identify the infiniteloop root cause                  
                                - In PPTXMLDump.dump(), when parsing                  
                             a malformed record header whose computed                  
                             `size` is negative (or zero), the code                    
                             does `continue;` without advancing `pos`.                 
                             This causes the `while` loop condition to                 
                             remain true indefinitely, hanging the                     
                             fuzzer and triggering a timeout.                          
                                                                                       
                             2. Preserve existing parsing logic                        
                                - We must still parse wellformed                      
                             records by reading the header, allocating                 
                             buffers, dumping XML, and advancing `pos                  
                             += size`.                                                 
                                - We should not modify harness code,                   
                             fuzzing flags, or external libraries.                     
                             Only the recorditeration logic in                        
                             PPTXMLDump must be patched.                               
                                                                                       
                             3. Update invalidheader handling                         
                                - Replace the `if (size < 0) {                         
                             continue; }` guard with a stronger check                  
                             that handles nonpositive sizes and                       
                             breaks out of the loop.                                   
                                - Specifically, change to:                             
                                  ```                                                  
                                  if (size <= 0) {                                     
                                      // malformed or zerolength                      
                             record: abort iteration to avoid infinite                 
                             loop                                                      
                                      break;                                           
                                  }                                                    
                                  ```                                                  
                                - This preserves normal parsing for                    
                             `size > 0` but ensures that on invalid                    
                             headers the loop exits immediately,                       
                             preventing the infinite loop.                             
                                                                                       
                             4. Implementation steps                                   
                                a. Open                                                
                             `poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/                 
                             poi/hslf/dev/PPTXMLDump.java`.                            
                                b. Locate the loop beginning at line                   
                             112 and the check at line ~127.                           
                                c. Modify lines 127131 from:                          
                                   ```                                                 
                                   if (size < 0) {                                     
                                       // stop processing of invalid                   
                             header data                                               
                                       continue;                                       
                                   }                                                   
                                   ```                                                 
                                   to:                                                 
                                   ```                                                 
                                   if (size <= 0) {                                    
                                       // malformed or zerolength                     
                             record: abort iteration to avoid infinite                 
                             loop                                                      
                                       break;                                          
                                   }                                                   
                                   ```                                                 
                                d. Ensure that `pos` remains                           
                             unmodified in this branch (break exits                    
                             loop), and that downstream logic for                      
                             valid `size` still does `pos += size`.                    
                                                                                       
                             5. Regression and sideeffect                             
                             considerations                                            
                                - Exiting the loop early on a                          
                             malformed header will skip any subsequent                 
                             records, but this is acceptable because                   
                             those records cannot be reliably parsed                   
                             anyway.                                                   
                                - No existing unit tests should fail,                  
                             as no test should depend on continuing                    
                             past invalid data.                                        
                                - Fuzzer harness, logging, and other                   
                             modules remain untouched; fuzzing runs                    
                             will now terminate promptly on corrupt                    
                             inputs instead of hanging.                                
                                                                                       
                             6. Justification                                          
                                - Breaking on invalid or zerolength                   
                             records is a standard defensiveparsing                   
                             pattern (mirrored in other recordbased                   
                             parsers).                                                 
                                - This change directly addresses the                   
                             infinite-loop symptom causing libFuzzer                   
                             timeouts without altering functional                      
                             parsing paths.                                            
                                - It does not introduce broad                          
                             exception catching, does not affect                       
                             harness code, and maintains compatibility                 
                             with existing tests.                                      
                                                                                       
                             7. No additional file retrieval is                        
                             necessary, as the loop context is fully                   
                             covered by the provided snippets.                         
                                                                                       
                             </fix_strategy>

                             ===Patch Result===                                        
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             ===Issue===                                               
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                   
                             # Evaluation Report                                       
                                                                                       
                             ## Summary                                                
                             The projects libFuzzer harness                           
                             consistently reports a timeout when                       
                             running against the `PPTXMLDump` code in                  
                             the `poi-scratchpad` module. An attempted                 
                             patch changed the handling of zero-length                 
                             record headers from skipping to breaking                  
                             out of the loop (to prevent a suspected                   
                             infinite loop). After applying the patch,                 
                             the fuzzer still times out, indicating                    
                             the change did not resolve the underlying                 
                             issue.                                                    
                                                                                       
                             ## Description                                            
                                                                                       
                             Initial Issue                                             
                             - During fuzzing with libFuzzer, the                      
                             process hangs until it reaches the                        
                             configured timeout.                                       
                             - The only error reported is ERROR:                      
                             libFuzzer: timeout, with no stack trace                  
                             or exception information.                                 
                             - No other errors are emitted by the Java                 
                             code; the harness simply stops making                     
                             progress.                                                 
                                                                                       
                             Important Observations                                    
                             - The timeout suggests the code under                     
                             test enters a long-running or infinite                    
                             loop in some input-specific code path.                    
                             - The fuzzer harness serves as the entry                  
                             point and repeatedly invokes                              
                             `PPTXMLDump`; it is not itself the root                   
                             cause.                                                    
                             - No other exceptions or resource                         
                             failures are reported, reinforcing that                   
                             control flow is stuck rather than                         
                             crashing.                                                 
                                                                                       
                             Patch Attempt                                             
                             - File modified:                                          
                             `poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/                 
                             poi/hslf/dev/PPTXMLDump.java`                             
                             - Original code (lines ~124132):                         
                               ```                                                     
                                           if (size < 0) {                             
                                               // stop processing of                   
                             invalid header data                                       
                                               continue;                               
                                           }                                           
                               ```                                                     
                             - Patched code:                                           
                               ```                                                     
                                           if (size <= 0) {                            
                                               // malformed or                         
                             zero-length record: abort iteration to                    
                             avoid infinite loop                                       
                                               break;                                  
                                           }                                           
                               ```                                                     
                             - Rationale: change the condition to                      
                             catch zero-length records as well as                      
                             negative sizes, and exit the loop rather                  
                             than skip, in order to prevent looping                    
                             indefinitely on corrupt input.                            
                                                                                       
                             Result After Patch                                        
                             - Fuzzer run still ends with ERROR:                      
                             libFuzzer: timeout.                                      
                             - No change in behavior other than the                    
                             patch application; the harness still does                 
                             not complete within the timeout window.                   
                                                                                       
                             Areas for Further Investigation                           
                             - The record-parsing loop in `PPTXMLDump`                 
                             (especially the logic around `pos`,                       
                             `size`, and loop termination).                            
                             - Other loops or recursive calls in                       
                             `PPTXMLDump` that process slide or shape                  
                             records.                                                  
                             - The sequence of `pos` increments and                    
                             bounds checks in the same method (to                      
                             ensure `pos` always advances).                            
                             - Interaction between multiple record                     
                             containers or nested structures in the                    
                             HSLF parser.                                              
                             - The fuzzers input handling code to                     
                             confirm that the data passed into                         
                             `PPTXMLDump` matches expectations for                     
                             boundary checks.                                          
                                                                                       
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                      
                             Here is the initial issue log of the                      
                             codebase:                                                 
                             <issue>                                                   
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             </issue>                                                  
                                                                                       
                             ## Additional Issue Log                                   
                             Here is the additional issue log after                    
                             the last patch attempt:                                   
                             <additional_issue>                                        
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             </additional_issue>                                       
                                                                                       
                             ## Notes                                                  
                             - All patch attempts are applied to the                   
                             initial codebase. Reapply the the                         
                             previous patches if needed.                               
                             - If multiple different issues are                        
                             present, all the issues must be resolved                  
                             in a single patch attempt.                                
                             - Try different approaches to resolve the                 
                             issues.                                                   
                             ===Analysis Report===                                     
                             # Analysis Report                                         
                                                                                       
                             ## Relevant Code Snippets                                 
                             <code_snippets>

                             ```                                                       
                             112:    public void dump(byte[] data, int                 
                             offset, int length, int padding) throws                   
                             IOException {                                             
                             113:        int pos = offset;                             
                             114:        while (pos <= (offset +                       
                             length - HEADER_SIZE)){                                   
                             115:            if (pos < 0) {                            
                             116:                break;                                
                             117:            }                                         
                             118:

                             120:            int info =                                
                             LittleEndian.getUShort(data, pos);                        
                             121:            pos +=                                    
                             LittleEndianConsts.SHORT_SIZE;                            
                             122:            int type =                                
                             LittleEndian.getUShort(data, pos);                        
                             123:            pos +=                                    
                             LittleEndianConsts.SHORT_SIZE;                            
                             124:            int size =                                
                             (int)LittleEndian.getUInt(data, pos);                     
                             125:            pos +=                                    
                             LittleEndianConsts.INT_SIZE;                              
                             126:                                                      
                             127:            if (size < 0) {                           
                             128:                // stop processing of                 
                             invalid header data                                       
                             129:                continue;                             
                             130:            }                                         
                             131:

                             RecordTypes.forTypeID(type).name();

                             " info=\""+info+"\" type=\""+type+"\"                     
                             size=\""+size+"\"                                         
                             offset=\""+(pos-8)+"\"", padding);                        
                             135:            if (hexHeader){                           
                             136:                out.write("                           
                             header=\"");                                              
                             137:                dump(out, data,                       
                             pos-8, 8, 0, false);                                      
                             138:                out.write("\"");                      
                             139:            }                                         
                             140:            out.write(">" + CR);                      
                             141:            padding++;

                             145:                //continue to dump                    
                             child records                                             
                             146:                dump(data, pos, size,                 
                             padding);                                                 
                             147:            } else {

                             <code>                                                    
                             poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/p                 
                             oi/hslf/dev/PPTXMLDump.java:165-193                       
                             ```                                                       
                             165:    public void dumpPictures(byte[]                   
                             data, int padding) throws IOException {                   
                             166:        int pos = 0;                                  
                             167:        while (pos < data.length) {                   
                             168:            if(data.length - pos <                    
                             PICT_HEADER_SIZE) {                                       
                             169:                // corrupt file,                      
                             cannot read header                                        
                             170:                return;                               
                             171:            }                                         
                             172:            byte[] header =                           
                             Arrays.copyOfRange(data, pos, pos +                       
                             PICT_HEADER_SIZE);                                        
                             173:            int size =                                
                             LittleEndian.getInt(header, 4) - 17;                      
                             174:            if(size < 0) {                            
                             175:                // corrupt file,                      
                             negative image size                                       
                             176:                return;                               
                             177:            }                                         
                             178:                                                      
                             179:            pos += PICT_HEADER_SIZE +                 
                             size;                                                     
                             180:                                                      
                             181:            padding++;                                
                             182:            write(out, "<picture                      
                             size=\""+size+"\"                                         
                             type=\""+getPictureType(header)+"\">" +                   
                             CR, padding);                                             
                             183:            padding++;                                
                             184:            write(out, "<header>" +                   
                             CR, padding);                                             
                             185:            dump(out, header, 0,                      
                             header.length, padding, true);                            
                             186:            write(out, "</header>" +                  
                             CR, padding);                                             
                             187:            write(out, "<imgdata>" +                  
                             CR, padding);                                             
                             188:            dump(out, data, 0,                        
                             Math.min(size, 100), padding, true);                      
                             189:            write(out, "</imgdata>" +                 
                             CR, padding);                                             
                             190:            padding--;                                
                             191:            write(out, "</picture>" +                 
                             CR, padding);                                             
                             192:            padding--;                                
                             193:        }                                             
                             ```                                                       
                             </code>                                                   
                             </code_snippets>                                          
                                                                                       
                             ## Fix Strategy                                           
                             <fix_strategy>                                            
                                                                                       
                             1. Core Issue Identification                              
                                - Infinite loop originates in the                      
                             `dump(byte[] data, int offset, int                        
                             length, int padding)` method of                           
                             `PPTXMLDump.java` when it encounters a                    
                             zerolength or otherwise malformed record                 
                             header.                                                   
                                - The existing size <= 0  break                     
                             patch only exits the *current* loop                       
                             invocation. In nested (container) calls,                  
                             the parent frame still resumes, leaving                   
                             `pos += size` with `size == 0`, so `pos`                  
                             never advances and the loop never                         
                             terminates.                                               
                                                                                       
                             2. Fix Approach                                           
                                A. Replace the size <= 0 break logic                 
                             with a *skip* logic that always advances                  
                             `pos` by the header size, then                            
                             *continues* the loop, ensuring progress.                  
                                B. Add a sanity check to catch                         
                             *oversized* records (cases where `size`                   
                             exceeds the remaining bytes in this                       
                             segment) to prevent illegal recursions or                 
                             intoverflow on `pos += size`.                            
                                                                                       
                             3. Detailed Steps                                         
                                In                                                     
                             `poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/                 
                             poi/hslf/dev/PPTXMLDump.java`, inside the                 
                             `dump(...)` method (around lines                          
                             124132):                                                 
                                1. Compute the remaining byte count in                 
                             this invocation:                                          
                                     `int remaining = offset + length                  
                             - pos;`                                                   
                                2. Replace the existing size check                     
                             block                                                     
                                     ```                                               
                                     if (size <= 0) {                                  
                                         // malformed or zero-length                   
                             record: abort iteration to avoid infinite                 
                             loop                                                      
                                         break;                                        
                                     }                                                 
                                     ```                                               
                                   with the following:                                 
                                     ```                                               
                                     // Sanitycheck record size: skip                 
                             if zero, negative, or extends beyond this                 
                             segment                                                   
                                     int remaining = offset + length -                 
                             pos;                                                      
                                     if (size <= 0 || size >                           
                             remaining) {                                              
                                         // malformed record: skip                     
                             header only, then continue parsing                        
                                         // pos was already advanced                   
                             by HEADER_SIZE                                            
                                         continue;                                     
                                     }                                                 
                                     ```                                               
                                3. Leave the rest of the loop logic                    
                             (container detection, recursion, atom                     
                             dump, closing tag, and `pos += size`)                     
                             *unchanged*.                                              
                                                                                       
                             4. Preservation of Existing Functionality                 
                                - Valid records (size > 0 and fitting                  
                             within the declared segment) are still                    
                             processed exactly as beforenames, hex                    
                             headers, recursion, atom data, and                        
                             closing tags are all intact.                              
                                - Negativesize records continue to be                 
                             skipped (as before).                                      
                                - Zerolength or overlength records                   
                             now advance past their headers (by virtue                 
                             of `continue`), guaranteeing `pos`                        
                             monotonically increases and eliminating                   
                             infinite loops, without invoking nested                   
                             recursion or writing bogus XML.                           
                                                                                       
                             5. Mitigation of Side Effects                             
                                - By skipping over malformed or                        
                             oversized records instead of attempting                   
                             to dump them or recursing on them, we may                 
                             omit some tags in the XML                                 
                             outputacceptable in a dump/debug tool,                 
                             especially under fuzz conditions.                         
                                - No external or harness code changes;                 
                             only the core parser is hardened.                         
                                - No broad exceptioncatching is                       
                             added, so underlying IO or programming                    
                             errors will still surface as before.                      
                                                                                       
                             6. Rationale                                              
                                - Using `continue` ensures                             
                             loopprogress in every iteration (header                  
                             size is already consumed), thereby                        
                             preventing any scenario where `pos`                       
                             remains unchanged.                                        
                                - Bounding `size` by `remaining`                       
                             prevents outofbounds reads or                           
                             intoverflows on depth recursions,                        
                             further eliminating nonterminating                       
                             patterns when a malformed container                     
                             recurses on garbage length.                               
                                - This aligns with existing handling                   
                             of negative sizes (skipping them), simply                 
                             extending it to zero and oversized cases.                 
                                                                                       
                             This single change addresses the timeout                  
                             by guaranteeing loop termination on                       
                             problematic records, preserves all                        
                             original parsing logic for wellformed                    
                             records, and requires no modifications to                 
                             tests, harnesses, or external libraries.                  
                                                                                       
                             </fix_strategy>

                                          //get name of the record by                  
                             type                                                      
                                          String recname =                             
                             RecordTypes.forTypeID(type).name();                       
                                          write(out, "<"+recname + "                   
                             info=\""+info+"\" type=\""+type+"\"                       
                             size=\""+size+"\"                                         
                             offset=\""+(pos-8)+"\"", padding);                        
                                                                                       
                             ===Patch Result===                                        
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             ===Issue===                                               
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                   
                             # Evaluation Report                                       
                                                                                       
                             ## Summary                                                
                             The projects fuzzing harness (via                        
                             libFuzzer) encountered a timeout without                  
                             producing a crash or hang trace. In                       
                             response, a patch was applied to                          
                             `PPTXMLDump.java` to strengthen the                       
                             recordsize sanity checkskipping records                 
                             that are zerolength, negative, or extend                 
                             beyond the current data segment. After                    
                             rebuilding with this change, libFuzzer                    
                             still reports ERROR: libFuzzer:                          
                             timeout, indicating the patch did not                    
                             resolve the timeout issue.                                
                                                                                       
                             ## Description                                            
                                                                                       
                             Initial Issue                                             
                             - The fuzzing session terminates with                     
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout, meaning the                  
                             target code did not complete processing                   
                             within the allotted time.                                 
                             - No crash or exception is reported; only                 
                             a timeout is observed.                                    
                             - The timeout suggests that under certain                 
                             inputs, the parsing loop in the HSLF                      
                             PPTXML dump tool takes excessively long                   
                             or never terminates.                                      
                                                                                       
                             Key Observations                                          
                             - The timeout occurs deep in the                          
                             PPTXMLDump routine, not in the harness                    
                             itself.                                                   
                             - The harness code merely invokes the                     
                             parser; it is not believed to be the root                 
                             cause.                                                    
                             - Timeouts often indicate either an                       
                             infinite loop, extreme processing of                      
                             malformed input, or very large                            
                             allocations.                                              
                                                                                       
                             Patch Attempt                                             
                             - File modified:                                          
                             `poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/                 
                             poi/hslf/dev/PPTXMLDump.java`                             
                             - Original code guarded only for `size <                  
                             0`.                                                       
                             - Patched code adds a check for `size <=                  
                             0` and `size > remaining`, where                          
                                 `remaining = offset + length - pos`                  
                             - If the check fails, the code now                        
                             executes `continue;` to skip only the                     
                             malformed header, rather than halting or                  
                             processing a bogus record.                                
                             - Context around modified lines:                          
                               ```java                                                 
                               int size =                                              
                             (int)LittleEndian.getUInt(data, pos);                     
                               pos += LittleEndianConsts.INT_SIZE;                     
                               // Sanity-check record size: skip if                    
                             zero, negative, or extends beyond this                    
                             segment                                                   
                               int remaining = offset + length - pos;                  
                               if (size <= 0 || size > remaining) {                    
                                   // malformed record: skip header                    
                             only, then continue parsing                               
                                   continue;                                           
                               }                                                       
                               // get name of the record by type                       
                               String recname =                                        
                             RecordTypes.forTypeID(type).name();                       
                               write(out, "<"+recname + "                              
                             info=\""+info+"\" type=\""+type+"\"                       
                             size=\""+size+"\"                                         
                             offset=\""+(pos-8)+"\"", padding);                        
                               ```                                                     
                             - After recompiling with this change, the                 
                             fuzzing run still ends in a timeout                       
                             without differing output or crash.                        
                                                                                       
                             Log After Patch                                           
                             - The only log message is again ERROR:                   
                             libFuzzer: timeout.                                      
                             - No new exceptions, errors, or progress                  
                             indicators appear in the fuzzing output.                  
                                                                                       
                             Further Investigation Areas                               
                             1. The main parsing loop(s) in                            
                             `PPTXMLDump` (particularly around `pos`                   
                             updates and record iteration) to detect                   
                             potential infinite loops.                                 
                             2. Other size or boundary checks in                       
                             record handling routines (for example,                    
                             image data or text run parsing).                          
                             3. Datadriven loops elsewhere in the                     
                             HSLF code that consume untrusted input                    
                             lengths.                                                  
                             4. Any external resource decoding invoked                 
                             by the harness (fonts, images, embedded                   
                             objects) that could stall on malformed                    
                             streams.                                                  
                             5. Timeout thresholds or instrumentation                  
                             settings in the libFuzzer harness that                    
                             might be too aggressive or mask                           
                             underlying hangs.                                         
                                                                                       
                             ---                                                       
                                                                                       
                             Overall, while the patch extends the                      
                             sanity checks around record size, the                     
                             root cause of the timeout remains                         
                             unresolved. Further inspection of all                     
                             looping constructs and length validations                 
                             within PPTXMLDump and related                             
                             recordparsing modules is recommended to                  
                             identify potential infinite or overly                     
                             long processing paths.                                    
                                                                                       
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                      
                             Here is the initial issue log of the                      
                             codebase:                                                 
                             <issue>                                                   
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             </issue>                                                  
                                                                                       
                             ## Additional Issue Log

                             the last patch attempt:                                   
                             <additional_issue>

                             ## Notes                                                  
                             - All patch attempts are applied to the                   
                             initial codebase. Reapply the the                         
                             previous patches if needed.                               
                             - If multiple different issues are                        
                             present, all the issues must be resolved                  
                             in a single patch attempt.                                
                             - Try different approaches to resolve the                 
                             issues.

                             ## Fix Strategy                                           
                             <fix_strategy>                                            
                                                                                       
                             1. Revert the previous size  0 or >                     
                             remaining  continue patch, restoring                    
                             the code around lines 127130 in                          
                             PPTXMLDump.java to the original state                     
                             (only checking `size < 0` and                             
                             `continue`).                                              
                             2. Introduce a new, robust sanity-check                   
                             for every record that both:                               
                                a. Ensures that when a record is                       
                             malformed (size  0 or size > remaining                   
                             data), the parsing loop cannot get stuck                  
                             at the same `pos`.                                        
                                b. Either skips past the problematic                   
                             data **or** abandons further parsing so                   
                             that `dump(...)` returns in bounded time.                 
                             3. Implement this as follows in the                       
                             `dump(byte[] data, int offset, int                        
                             length, int padding)` method, immediately                 
                             after reading the 4-byte size field and                   
                             advancing `pos` by `INT_SIZE`:                            
                                ```java                                                
                                    // after: int size =                               
                             (int)LittleEndian.getUInt(data, pos);                     
                                    pos +=                                             
                             LittleEndianConsts.INT_SIZE;                              
                                    int remaining = offset + length -                  
                             pos;                                                      
                                                                                       
                                    // New sanity check: avoid                         
                             infinite loops on bad record sizes                        
                                    if (size <= 0 || size > remaining)                 
                             {                                                         
                                        // We've hit invalid data:                     
                             terminate the loop to prevent hanging                     
                                        break;                                         
                                    }                                                  
                                ```                                                    
                                - This replaces the old                                
                             `continue`-only approach. By breaking out                 
                             of the while-loop, `dump(...)` returns                    
                             promptly rather than looping on an                        
                             unchanged `pos`.                                          
                                - Alternatively (if you prefer to                      
                             process subsequent sibling records in a                   
                             container), you could jump to the end of                  
                             the segment and let the outer                             
                             while-condition exit naturally:                           
                                  ```java                                              
                                      if (size <= 0 || size >                          
                             remaining) {                                              
                                          pos = offset + length;                       
                                          continue;                                    
                                      }                                                
                                  ```                                                  
                             4. Verify that:                                           
                                - All existing valid parsing (positive                 
                             sizes within bounds) still executes the                   
                             body of the loop and does `pos += size;`                  
                             as before.                                                
                                - No other paths use `continue`                        
                             without advancing `pos`.                                  
                                - Edge cases (zerolength, oversized                   
                             fields) now terminate parsing rather than                 
                             stall.                                                    
                             5. Rationale:                                             
                                - The root cause of the timeout is an                  
                             infinite loop when parsing malformed                      
                             records: the code keeps re-reading the                    
                             same invalid header because `pos` never                   
                             moves past it.                                            
                                - By breaking out (or by advancing                     
                             `pos` to the end), we guarantee forward                   
                             progress and bounded execution time on                    
                             arbitrary fuzz inputs.                                    
                                - This change is localized to                          
                             PPTXMLDump, does not touch harness or                     
                             utility code, and preserves all existing                  
                             functionality for well-formed records.                    
                             6. Potential Side Effects & Mitigations:                  
                                - On encountering the first malformed                  
                             record, parsing stops. This may skip                      
                             valid records later in the same slide or                  
                             container. However, since fuzzing inputs                  
                             are often heavily corrupted, terminating                  
                             early is preferable to hanging                            
                             indefinitely.                                             
                                - If fine-grained recovery is                          
                             required, switch from `break` to the                      
                             jump to end and continue variant shown                  
                             above.                                                    
                             7. No changes to tests, harness, or                       
                             external libraries are neededonly                        
                             PPTXMLDump.java is modified. This ensures                 
                             existing unit tests and fuzz targets                      
                             continue to operate as before, without                    
                             timeouts.                                                 
                                                                                       
                             </fix_strategy>
