                             ===Patch Result===                                        
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             ===Issue===                                               
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                   
                             # Evaluation Report                                       
                                                                                       
                             ## Summary                                                
                                                                                       
                             The initial issue reported by libFuzzer                   
                             is a persistent timeout when fuzzing the                  
                             PPTXMLDump component of the Apache POI                    
                             codebase. In an attempt to prevent                        
                             infinite loops on malformed record                        
                             headers, a patch was applied to                           
                             `PPTXMLDump.java` that adds a sanity                      
                             check on the parsed record size (`size`)                  
                             and aborts the parsing loop if the size                   
                             is nonpositive or larger than the                        
                             remaining buffer. After applying this                     
                             patch, the fuzzer still reports a                         
                             timeout, indicating that the introduced                   
                             check did not resolve the hang.                           
                                                                                       
                             ## Description                                            
                                                                                       
                             1. Initial Issue                                          
                                - A libFuzzer run against the                          
                             `poi-scratchpad` module hangs                             
                             indefinitely, eventually reporting                        
                             `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`.                              
                                - The timeout indicates that some code                 
                             path in PPTXMLDump (or code it invokes)                   
                             enters a longrunning or infinite loop                    
                             for certain malformed or adversarial                      
                             inputs.                                                   
                                                                                       
                             2. Observations and Findings                              
                                - The timeout occurs during a fuzzing                  
                             session of the PPTXMLDump XML dump                        
                             routine (in                                               
                             `org/apache/poi/hslf/dev/PPTXMLDump.java`                 
                             ).                                                        
                                - No crash or exception is reported;                   
                             the code simply never completes                           
                             processing.                                               
                                - The fuzzers harness merely invokes                  
                             the dump method on arbitrary input                        
                             streams, making the hang reproducible on                  
                             specific inputs.                                          
                                                                                       
                             3. Patch Attempt                                          
                                - Location: `PPTXMLDump.java`, around                  
                             line 124 in the main recordprocessing                    
                             loop.                                                     
                                - Original code fragment:                              
                                  ```                                                  
                                  int size =                                           
                             (int)LittleEndian.getUInt(data, pos);                     
                                  pos += LittleEndianConsts.INT_SIZE;                  
                                  if (size < 0) {                                      
                                      // stop processing of invalid                    
                             header data                                               
                                      continue;                                        
                                  }                                                    
                                  ```                                                  
                                - Patched code adds a check against                    
                             the remaining unparsed buffer and breaks                  
                             out of the loop on invalid sizes:                         
                                  ```                                                  
                                  int size =                                           
                             (int)LittleEndian.getUInt(data, pos);                     
                                  pos += LittleEndianConsts.INT_SIZE;                  
                                  // Sanity-check record size: avoid                   
                             infinite loops on bad record sizes                        
                                  int remaining = offset + length -                    
                             pos;                                                      
                                  if (size <= 0 || size > remaining) {                 
                                      // invalid record: abort parsing                 
                             to avoid hang                                             
                                      break;                                           
                                  }                                                    
                                  ```                                                  
                                - The rest of the loop (recordtype                    
                             lookup, XML writing) remains unchanged.                   
                                                                                       
                             4. Result After Patch                                     
                                - The fuzzer run still ends with                       
                             `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`.                              
                                - No difference in behavior other than                 
                             possibly skipping the immediate                           
                             infiniteloop location.                                   
                                                                                       
                             5. Areas for Further Investigation                        
                                - The main recordparsing loop in                      
                             `PPTXMLDump` (and any recursive or nested                 
                             loops it invokes) for other conditions                    
                             that can lead to nontermination.                         
                                - Inputdriven loops in helper methods                 
                             (e.g., reading text properties, iterating                 
                             over shape records, processing complex                    
                             subrecords) where similar size or                        
                             boundary checks may be missing.                           
                                - Any use of `while(true)` or loops                    
                             conditioned on dynamic values derived                     
                             from untrusted input.                                     
                                - Interaction between `offset`,                        
                             `length`, and nested record                               
                             sequencesespecially once the toplevel                   
                             break fires, whether control flow enters                  
                             another unguarded loop.                                   
                                - Potential stateful accumulations                     
                             (e.g., lists of child records) that grow                  
                             without bound when encountering malformed                 
                             streams.                                                  
                                - The fuzzing harness to confirm it                    
                             exercises all entry points and record                     
                             types in PPTXMLDump, ensuring full                        
                             coverage of parsing code.                                 
                                                                                       
                             This report catalogs the unaltered                        
                             timeout issue, the precise patch applied,                 
                             and the continuing failure. It highlights                 
                             the need to broaden the inspection of                     
                             parsing loops and boundary checks                         
                             throughout the codebase for a complete                    
                             resolution.                                               
                                                                                       
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                      
                             Here is the initial issue log of the                      
                             codebase:                                                 
                             <issue>                                                   
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             </issue>                                                  
                                                                                       
                             ## Additional Issue Log                                   
                             Here is the additional issue log after                    
                             the last patch attempt:                                   
                             <additional_issue>                                        
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             </additional_issue>                                       
                                                                                       
                             ## Notes                                                  
                             - All patch attempts are applied to the                   
                             initial codebase. Reapply the the                         
                             previous patches if needed.                               
                             - If multiple different issues are                        
                             present, all the issues must be resolved                  
                             in a single patch attempt.                                
                             - Try different approaches to resolve the                 
                             issues.

                             </code_snippets>                                          
                                                                                       
                             ## Fix Strategy                                           
                             <fix_strategy>                                            
                                                                                       
                             1. Broaden and strengthen size/boundary                   
                             checks throughout all parsing loops in                    
                             PPTXMLDump:                                               
                                a. Main recordparsing loop                            
                             (`dump(byte[] data, int offset, int                       
                             length, int padding)`):                                   
                                   - Ensure the size check introduced                  
                             (i.e., `if (size <= 0 || size >                           
                             remaining) break;`) is indeed present                     
                             exactly at the top of the loop after                      
                             reading `size` and before any recursion                   
                             or writes.                                                
                                   - Also guard against the case where                 
                             `offset + length - HEADER_SIZE`                           
                             underflows (when `length < HEADER_SIZE`),                 
                             by adding an explicit earlyreturn if                     
                             `length < HEADER_SIZE`.                                   
                                b. Container recursion:                                
                                   - Apply the same `size <= 0 || size                 
                             > remaining` guard in every recursive                     
                             call to `dump(...)`, so that no nested                    
                             call ever processes invalid or                            
                             zerolength containers.                                   
                                c. Atomdata hex dump:                                 
                                   - Before calling `dump(out, data,                   
                             pos, Math.min(size, data.length - pos),                   
                             ...)`, ensure `pos >= 0` and `pos +                       
                             length_to_dump <= data.length`.                           
                                d. `dumpPictures(byte[] data, int                      
                             padding)`:                                                
                                   - Add a sanity check on `size`                      
                             against the remaining buffer:                             
                                     ```                                               
                                     int remaining = data.length - pos                 
                             - PICT_HEADER_SIZE;                                       
                                     if (size < 0 || size > remaining)                 
                             {                                                         
                                         // corrupt or adversarial                     
                             size: abort picture dump                                  
                                         return;                                       
                                     }                                                 
                                     ```                                               
                                   - This prevents `pos +=                             
                             PICT_HEADER_SIZE + size` from wrapping or                 
                             underflowing, eliminating infinite loops                  
                             in picture parsing.                                       
                             2. Improve overall loopexit conditions:                  
                                - In every whileloop driven by `pos <                 
                             limit`, verify before increment that                      
                             `nextPos = pos + advance` is strictly                     
                             greater than `pos`. If not, break to                      
                             avoid stalls.                                             
                                - For example, in `dumpPictures`:                      
                                  ```                                                  
                                  int nextPos = pos + PICT_HEADER_SIZE                 
                             + size;                                                   
                                  if (nextPos <= pos) break;                           
                                  pos = nextPos;                                       
                                  ```                                                  
                             3. Preserve existing functionality:                       
                                - No changes to harness or test code;                  
                             only PPTXMLDump.                                          
                                - Retain writing of valid records and                  
                             hex dumps for wellformed sizes.                          
                                - Ensure that legitimate 0length                      
                             containers (if any) are handled                           
                             gracefullyeither by design they should                   
                             never occur, or they should simply be                     
                             skipped.                                                  
                             4. Potential side effects and mitigation:                 
                                - Some malformed but nonmalicious                     
                             files that rely on zerolength                            
                             sub-records will now silently abort                       
                             further dumping; this is acceptable in a                  
                             fuzzing context to prevent hangs, and                     
                             such cases can be documented.                             
                                - Verify via unit tests on known PPT                   
                             samples and edgecases that no valid                      
                             scenarios are inadvertently skipped.                      
                             5. Testing and validation:                                
                                - Rerun libFuzzer on `PPTXMLDump` to                  
                             confirm no more timeout.                                  
                                - Add regression tests for:                            
                                   A record with size == 0 in                         
                             container context.                                        
                                   A `dumpPictures` input with header                 
                             size smaller than advertised `size`.                      
                                   Inputs where `offset+length <                      
                             HEADER_SIZE`.                                             
                             6. Documentation:                                         
                                - In method Javadoc for both                           
                             `dump(...)` and `dumpPictures(...)`,                      
                             document that records with invalid or                     
                             out-of-bounds sizes cause early exit to                   
                             avoid infinite loops.                                     
                                                                                       
                             Justification:                                            
                             - The fuzzer timeout indicated unbounded                  
                             loops on zero or out-of-range sizes;                      
                             tightening the loopexit conditions                       
                             everywhere ensures no `pos` can stagnate                  
                             or wrap.                                                  
                             - This preserves existing valid parsing                   
                             logic and only aborts on truly malformed                  
                             inputs.                                                   
                             - Similar bound checks already exist in                   
                             the main loop; extending them to helper                   
                             loops (like `dumpPictures`) and enforcing                 
                             monotonic `pos` progression universally                   
                             eliminates sources of nontermination.                    
                                                                                       
                             </fix_strategy>                                           
                             ===Evaluation End===

                             ===Patch Result===                                        
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             ===Issue===                                               
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                   
                             # Evaluation Report                                       
                                                                                       
                             ## Summary                                                
                             - **Initial issue:** While fuzzing the                    
                             PPTXMLDump component of Apache POI (via                   
                             libFuzzer), the harness consistently                      
                             times out rather than crashing or                         
                             completing.                                               
                             - **Patch attempt:** Bounds checks and                    
                             early exits were introduced in two                        
                             parsing routines`dump(byte[],)` and                     
                             `dumpPictures(byte[],)`to abort or                      
                             break out on invalid or out-of-range                      
                             sizes, with the aim of preventing                         
                             infinite loops.                                           
                             - **Result:** Even after applying these                   
                             guards and returning or breaking on bad                   
                             input, the fuzzer still reports a                         
                             timeout, indicating the hang condition                    
                             persists.                                                 
                                                                                       
                             ## Description                                            
                                                                                       
                             Initial Issue                                             
                             - The only symptom is a libFuzzer timeout                 
                             (no exception or crash).                                  
                             - The timeout points to a hang or                         
                             extremely slow path in the PPTXMLDump                     
                             parsing routines.                                         
                             - The harness simply calls methods in                     
                             `PPTXMLDump` on arbitrary byte arrays,                    
                             making these loops prime suspects.                        
                                                                                       
                             Patch Attempt                                             
                             - In `dump(byte[] data, int offset, int                   
                             length, int padding)`:                                    
                                If `length < HEADER_SIZE`, return                     
                             immediately.                                              
                                Before processing each record:                        
                             compute `remaining = offset + length -                    
                             pos`; if `size <= 0 || size > remaining`,                 
                             break out of the loop.                                    
                             - In `dumpPictures(byte[] data, int                       
                             padding)`:                                                
                                If remaining bytes <                                  
                             `PICT_HEADER_SIZE`, return.                               
                                Compute picture payload size; if                      
                             `size < 0 || size > remainingPic`,                        
                             return.                                                   
                                Calculate `nextPos = pos +                            
                             PICT_HEADER_SIZE + size`; if `nextPos <=                  
                             pos`, break to avoid stalls; otherwise                    
                             update `pos = nextPos`.                                   
                                                                                       
                             Log After Patch                                           
                             - The fuzz target still reports                           
                               `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`                             
                             - No change in behavior under fuzzing:                    
                             the parser still hangs or loops without                   
                             terminating promptly.                                     
                                                                                       
                             Key Observations & Next Steps                             
                             - The timeout indicates that at least one                 
                             parsing loop can still iterate                            
                             indefinitely or do extremely heavy work                   
                             on crafted inputs.                                        
                             - `dump(...)`s loop condition `while                     
                             (pos <= offset + length - HEADER_SIZE)`                   
                             may still not advance `pos` in some code                  
                             paths (e.g., when encountering unknown                    
                             record types or missing size updates).                    
                             - `dumpPictures(...)` may exit early on                   
                             some corrupt inputs but still hang on                     
                             others if neither the return nor break                    
                             conditions are triggered.                                 
                             - Other parts of `PPTXMLDump`especially                  
                             record-type dispatch and nested parsing                   
                             callsshould be reviewed to ensure every                  
                             path advances `pos` or terminates.                        
                             - Broader review of all loops driven by                   
                             parsed size fields (including any                         
                             sub-headers or footer blocks) is needed                   
                             to identify the remaining hang.                           
                                                                                       
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                      
                             Here is the initial issue log of the                      
                             codebase:                                                 
                             <issue>                                                   
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             </issue>                                                  
                                                                                       
                             ## Additional Issue Log                                   
                             Here is the additional issue log after                    
                             the last patch attempt:                                   
                             <additional_issue>                                        
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                 
                                                                                       
                             </additional_issue>                                       
                                                                                       
                             ## Notes                                                  
                             - All patch attempts are applied to the                   
                             initial codebase. Reapply the the                         
                             previous patches if needed.                               
                             - If multiple different issues are                        
                             present, all the issues must be resolved                  
                             in a single patch attempt.                                
                             - Try different approaches to resolve the                 
                             issues.

                             240:    private String                                    
                             getPictureType(byte[] header){                            
                             241:        String type;                                  
                             242:        int meta =                                    
                             LittleEndian.getUShort(header, 0);                        
                             243:                                                      
                             244:        switch(meta){                                 
                             245:            case 0x46A0: type =                       
                             "jpeg"; break;                                            
                             246:            case 0x2160: type =                       
                             "wmf"; break;                                             
                             247:            case 0x6E00: type =                       
                             "png"; break;                                             
                             248:            default: type =                           
                             "unknown"; break;                                         
                             249:        }                                             
                             250:        return type;                                  
                             251:    }                                                 
                             252:                                                      
                             253:    /**                                               
                             254:     *  dump binary data to {@code                    
                             out} with the specified padding                           
                             255:     */                                               
                             256:    private static void dump(Writer                   
                             out, byte[] data, int offset, int length,                 
                             int padding, boolean nl) throws                           
                             IOException {                                             
                             257:        int linesize = 25;                            
                             258:        for (int i = 0; i < padding;                  
                             i++) out.write("  ");                                     
                             259:        int i;                                        
                             260:        for (i = offset; i < (offset                  
                             + length); i++) {                                         
                             261:            int c = data[i];                          
                             262:            out.write((char)                          
                             hexval[(c & 0xF0) >> 4]);                                 
                             263:            out.write((char)                          
                             hexval[(c & 0x0F) >> 0]);                                 
                             264:            out.write(' ');                           
                             265:            if((i+1-offset) %                         
                             linesize == 0 && i != (offset +                           
                             length-1)) {                                              
                             266:                out.write(CR);                        
                             267:                for (int j = 0; j <                   
                             padding; j++) out.write("  ");                            
                             268:            }                                         
                             269:        }                                             
                             270:        if(nl && length >                             
                             0)out.write(CR);                                          
                             271:    }

                             ## Fix Strategy                                           
                             <fix_strategy>                                            
                                                                                       
                             1. Reintroduce and preserve the existing                  
                             sizeguards in both parsing routines.                     
                                a. In `dump(byte[] data, int offset,                   
                             int length, int padding)`:                                
                                   - Keep the early-return when                        
                             `length < HEADER_SIZE`.                                   
                                   - Keep the break when `size <= 0                  
                             || size > remaining`, to ensure the main                  
                             whileloop cannot stall on zero or huge                   
                             sizes.                                                    
                                b. In `dumpPictures(byte[] data, int                   
                             padding)`:                                                
                                   - Keep the checks for `size <= 0 ||                 
                             size > remainingPic` and the `nextPos <=                  
                             pos` guard, so outofrange or                            
                             nonadvancing sizes abort the loop.                       
                                                                                       
                             2. Cap all hexdump operations to a                       
                             small, fixed maximum.                                     
                                a. Define a classlevel constant, e.g.                 
                                   ```java                                             
                                   private static final int                            
                             MAX_HEX_DUMP_BYTES = 100;                                 
                                   ```                                                 
                                b. In the noncontainer branch of                      
                             `dump(...)` (around line 147): replace                    
                                   ```java                                             
                                   dump(out, data, pos, Math.min(size,                 
                             data.length - pos), padding, true);                       
                                   ```                                                 
                                   with                                                
                                   ```java                                             
                                   int avail = Math.min(size,                          
                             data.length - pos);                                       
                                   int dumpLen = Math.min(avail,                       
                             MAX_HEX_DUMP_BYTES);                                      
                                   dump(out, data, pos, dumpLen,                       
                             padding, true);                                           
                                   ```                                                 
                                c. (Optionally) Similarly cap any                      
                             recursive hexdump in `dump(out, data,                    
                             pos-8, 8)` if `hexHeader` is ever                        
                             enlargedthough headers are fixed at 8                    
                             bytes.                                                    
                                                                                       
                             3. (Optional extra safety) In the main                    
                             `dump(...)` loop, after `pos += size`,                    
                             add a sanity check:                                       
                                ```java                                                
                                if (pos <= lastPos) {                                  
                                    // size was zero or                                
                             overflowedexit to prevent any risk of                    
                             hang                                                      
                                    break;                                             
                                }                                                      
                                ```                                                    
                                where `lastPos` is the value of `pos`                  
                             immediately before size addition.                         
                                                                                       
                             4. Do not modify harness or fuzzing                       
                             logicthese changes are entirely within                   
                             `PPTXMLDump.java`. No external                            
                             dependencies or tests are altered.                        
                                                                                       
                             Justification:                                            
                             - The persistent fuzzer timeout is caused                 
                             not by an infiniteloop delta in record                   
                             navigation (sizeguards already prevent                   
                             true nonadvancing loops), but by too                     
                             much work in hexdumping large record                     
                             payloads. Under adversarial inputs, the                   
                             call                                                      
                               `dump(out, data, pos, Math.min(size,                    
                             data.lengthpos), )`                                     
                               can iterate over thousands of bytes per                 
                             record and do expensive writes, leading                   
                             to timeout rather than crash.                             
                             - By capping every hexdump to at most                    
                             100 bytes (matching the existing cap used                 
                             in picturedata dumps), we guarantee that                 
                             each record contributes only bounded                      
                             work, restoring fuzzer throughput without                 
                             eliminating structure output for small,                   
                             valid records.                                            
                             - All original parsing logic,                             
                             containervsatom dispatch, and                           
                             outofrange checks remain in place, so                   
                             valid PPT XML dumps are unaffected.                       
                             Timeouts on synthetic or malicious inputs                 
                             are eliminated.                                           
                             - Potential side effects: outputs for                     
                             very large record payloads will be                        
                             truncated in the hex dump. This is                        
                             consistent with `dumpPictures` (which                     
                             already limits to 100 bytes), and                         
                             preserves the core functionality of                       
                             structure dumping while preventing                        
                             pathological slowdowns.                                   
                                                                                       
                             No harness, test, or external library                     
                             modifications are required. This strategy                 
                             reuses and extends existing defensive                     
                             checks and addresses the only remaining                   
                             slow path.                                                
                                                                                       
                             </fix_strategy>
